## Subgroup Series

We often come across (Mizar) functors which define a subgroup, like the
derived subgroup, or `center`, etc. Let `F(G)` denote this functor
acting on a given group. We use these to define a subnormal
subgroup series `U`:

- `U.0 = (1).G`
- `U.(n+1) ./. U.n = F(G ./. U.n)`

The other approach is to construct a "lower series" by

- `L.0 = G`
- `L.(n+1) = F(L.n)`

